Here’s a basic example:

$(document).ready(function() {
    $('#elementToApplyHere').hideMaxListItems({ 'max':4 });
});

There are 3 available options; the maximum number of list items to show, the speed 
of the slide animation in milliseconds, and the HTML used for the expand/collapse 
link. I could have given an option for the text inside of the link instead, but I 
wanted to allow for more customization if you want to change the HTML. It defaults 
to a max of 5, a speed of 1000 (ms), and a paragraph containing a link with “READ 
MORE”. Note that the expand/collapse container needs the “maxlist-more” class, and 
a child anchor tag. Here’s an example with the options:

$(document).ready(function() {
    $('#content ul').hideMaxListItems({
        'max':6,
        'speed':2000,
        'moreHTML': '<p class="maxlist-more"><a href="#">MORE OF THEM</a></p>'
    });
});